playerName=eddie+rodriguez&playerStats=index.html&previous=melvin&next=welch&playerBio=first base coach
born: March 11, 1959; Havana, Cuba
lives: Mesa
former position: outfielder

Brought on to the staff after spending last summer as third base coach for Tommy Lasorda and the U.S. Olympics team. The team went 7-1 overall, featuring a 4-0 win over Cuba in the championship game. Previously managed Queens, one of Toronto's short-season A clubs. Spent 15 years in the California Angels' organization, twice doing double-duty as a player/coach.
